-- Turkish Stocks: Banvit Bandirma, Goldas Kuyumculuk, Mepet Move
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-07-17T15:32:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-17/turkish-stocks-banvit-bandirma-goldas-kuyumculuk-mepet-move.html
Turkeyâ€™s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  fell 0.3 percent to 62,472.82 at the close in Istanbul,
breaking two days of gains.  The following shares were active. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  Banvit Bandirma Vitaminli Yem Sanayii AS (BANVT)  , a
Turkish poultry producer, climbed as much as 1.7 percent before
paring gains to 0.7 percent at 4.12 liras after announcing it
will set up a company in the United Arab Emirates to market its
products in Gulf countries.  Goldas Kuyumculuk AS (GOLDS)  , a Turkish producer of gold
and silver jewelry, rose 1.8 percent to 0.56 liras after saying
its owner Yalinkaya Group started cooperation talks with London-
based Delamore & Owl Group of Companies.  Mepet Metro Petrol & Tesisleri Sanayi & Ticaret AS (MEPET)  , a fuel retailer, rose the most in almost six weeks, gaining
3.7 percent to 1.67 liras after saying it plans a gas station,
shopping mall, hotel and mosque project in Saudi Arabia with a
partner.  To contact the reporter on this story:
